parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause loss of power, stalling, and potentially lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: white smoke coming out of the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine failure, which can cause loss of power, stalling, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: the oil light does not come on
and the engine may misfire or stall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to stall, making it difficult or impossible to continue driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the steering coupler can cause the steering wheel to shake, vibrate, or make a clicking noise, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Clicking or clunking noise when turning the steering wheel
vibration or shaking of the steering wheel

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The erratic steering can cause the vehicle to wander or drift out of its lane, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Vehicle wanders or drifts out of its lane

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: loud clicking or grinding noise when turning the steering wheel
and loss of power steering assist.
